<TITLE>Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Malta - Head Office</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P>
<A NAME="link_1"></A>

<CENTER><H2><B>ORGANIZATIONAL CHART OF<br>
THE MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS OF MALTA</B></H2></CENTER>



<CENTER><IMG SRC="org1.gif"></CENTER>

<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_18"></A>
<B> MR SALV J. STELLINI</B>
<P>
<B>Permanent Secretary</B>
<P>

<IMG SRC="amb/stellini.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born July 1939; Salv
Stellini graduated B.A. (Hons) from the Royal University of Malta
in 1964 and M.A. from the University of Alberta (Canada) joining
the Ministry in 1966 as Second Secretary.  After undertaking a
one-year course in international relations, short-term assignments
in Canberra and Dar-as-Salaam, he was posted to the Malta U.N.
Mission in New York.  Mr Stellini returned to Head Office ('71-'74)
and was posted as First Secretary to the London High Commission.
 In 1977 he was seconded to the Commonwealth Secretariat and returned
to Head Office by 1979. 1981 saw Mr Stellini's resignation yet
he rejoined the service in 1988 and was subsequently appointed
Ambassador to the U.S.A. and in 1991 High Commissioner in London,
where he stayed till September 1996.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>






<P>
<A NAME="link_20"></A>
<B>MR SAVIOUR BORG</B>
<P>
<B> Director of Multilateral Affairs</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/borg-s.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Saviour F. Borg joined
the Maltese Civil Service in 1965, serving in the Ministries of
Health, Agriculture and Fisheries and the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs where he served as Section Head of the Eastern and North
European and Nordic countries.  Mr Borg has served in the Foreign
service since 1977.  Between 1978-1982 he was posted as Deputy
Permanent Representative of Malta to the United Nations 0ffice,
and other international organisations in Geneva.  For the period
1983-1987, he served as Deputy Permanent Representative to the
U.N. in New York.  In 1988 he was appointed Head of the U.N. International
Organisations and Commonwealth Division and in February 1994 as
Director of Multilateral Affairs.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_22"></A>
<B>MR ALFRED ZARB</B>
<P>
<B>Director of Bilateral Relations</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/zarb.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Studied at the Lyceum and
worked for the Admiralty before joining the civil service in 1960
at the Passport and Immigration Office.  In 1964 was posted to
New York to serve in the new U.N. Permanent Mission.  Assisted
in the setting  up of the Washington Embassy before returning
to Head Office in Malta in 1968.  Served in the new Permanent
Delegation in Geneva from January 1970 to August 1975 and again
as Charge d'Affaires during 1977.  At Head Office occupied various
positions moving from consular relations, personal assistant to
the Secretary, Arab Desk Officer, Head of the Mediterranean Section
onto the Maghreb and Africa division.  In 1989, he was responsible
for Latin America, Africa and Asia before taking up the Directorship
of Bilateral Relations in 1992.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_16"></A>
<B>MR GAETAN A. NAUDI</B>
<P>
<B>Director of Corporate Services</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/naudi.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Appointed Director of Corporate
Services on a three-year Performance Contract in the Ministry
of Foreign Affairs in November 1993. Entered the Malta Civil Service
as a Clerk Typist in 1964, and from there progressed through a
variety of administrative and managerial roles, assuming responsibility
for activities mainly in the fields of financial management, human
resource administration and internal audit.  Between 1990 and
late 1993, he was Manager of the Finance and Administration Division
in the Management Systems Unit Limited, and was the Secretary
of the Board of Directors of the Company before rejoining the
Service to come to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.  Gaetan Naudi
is a qualified Chartered Secretary and was elected Associate of
the Institute of Chartered Secretaries and Administrators of the
UK in September 1972.  Born on 24 October 1946 in Hamrun, Malta,
he is married to Imelda nee Camilleri.  They have two sons, Rodney
James and Gilbert John.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>




<P>
<A NAME="link_21"></A>
<B>MR ALFRED CACHIA</B>
<P>
<B>Head of Protocol</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/cachia-a.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born in Sliema, February
7, 1939 Alfred Cachia was educated at St Albert the Great College.
 He commenced his service career with the government as clerical
officer between 1957 and 1959.  In 1967 he was promoted to the
grade of a Higher Clerical Officer (1967-1972) until joining the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs as Protocol Secretary in 1972.  By
1983, Alfred Cachia was promoted Head of Protocol.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>




