<TITLE>Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Malta - Diplomatic Network</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ebc79c">

<P>
<A NAME="link_1"></A>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="world1.gif"></CENTER>

<HR noshade size=5>



<P>
<A NAME="link_23"></A>
<B>MR MAURICE ABELA</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador to OSCE</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/abela.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born on November 24, 1926,Maurice
Abela obtained a degree in Economics at Hull University. He joined
the Civil Service as a clerk in 1945 and by 1959 was appointed
Principal Government Statistician and Electoral Officer. In June
1966, he was promoted to Principal Assistant Secretary responsible
for setting-up an Economic Planning division at OPM. Within the
international sphere he joined Observer teams to supervise elections
in British Guinea (1964) and the Mauritius (1966).  In February
1971, he was appointed Secretary and designated Secretary to the
Cabinet.  By 1973 he served as Secretary at the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs; and between 1973-1974 he was selected as Chairman of
the National Bank of Malta and the Bank of Valletta.  In January
1984 he was appointed Executive Secretary and later Secretary
General at OPM.  He was Ambassador in Rome for the period 1987-1993.
 He is married to Helene nee Madiona and has four children.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_24"></A>
<TT> </TT><B>MR CARMEL AQUILINA</B>
<P>
<B> Ambassador Rome</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/aquilina.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born 6 April 1939, Carmel
Aquilina was educated at The Lyceum, Royal University of Malta
and Hunter College, New York.  Hubert H. Humphrey Fellow 198511986.
 Joined the Malta Civil Service in 1957 and served in various
Government Departments including the Ministry of Commonwealth
and Foreign Affairs (1967-1977) and Works Department.  Rejoined
Ministry of Foreign Affairs in 1987.  First Counsellor (Rome)
1987-1990, Director Europe and North America Division (1990-1992)
and Acting Secretary (April 1992 - May 1993).  Mr Aquilina is
currently Malta's resident Ambassador in Rome, accredited also
to Switzerland, Portugal, Israel, Albania, Greece and Cyprus.
 Mr Aquilina is married to Pauline nee Zammit and has three children.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_25"></A>
<B>MR MICHAEL BARTOLO</B>
<P>
<B>Permanent Representative of Malta to the United Nations (Geneva)</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/bartolo.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born on the 21st May
1939 in Malta, Michael Bartolo has carried out a large portion
of his service career permanently based to the United Nations
and other international organisations; holding various posts in
the area of Economic and Social Affairs and most recently as Deputy
Director of Policy, Programming and Development Planning.  During
the period 1990-1994 he served as Principal Adviser to the President
of the 45th Session of the U.N. General Assembly; Special Adviser
to the Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs and
currently fulfilling the post of President, central Examination
Board of the United Nations.<BR><P>

Visit the <A HREF="http://www.itu.ch/MISSIONS/Malta/index.html"><B>home page of the Permanent Mission</B></A>
 of Malta to UN Office and other international organizations at Geneva
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_26"></A>
<B>DR ALBERT BORG OLIVIER DE PUGET</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador Washington</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/depugot.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Dr A. Borg Olivier de
Puget was born on April 15, 1932. His public activities included
serving as a Member of Parliament for the period 1966-1981, during
which time he was also active internationally participating as
Member of the Parliamentary delegations to the Assembly of the
Council of Europe, to the Second Congress of Parliamentarians
of the European Movement, to Egypt and the Libyan Arab Republic
as well as the 21st and 24th Commonwealth Parliamentary Conferences.
 He was appointed Magistrate on 9 November 1983.  Between 1987-1991
he was Ambassador to France whilst simultaneously accredited to
Spain, Portugal and Switzerland.  In this period, he was also
appointed Malta's Permanent Delegate to UNESCO.  By October 1991
he was designated Ambassador to the U.S.A. and High Commissioner
to Canada as from March 1992.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_27"></A>
<B>MR GEORGE BUSUTTIL</B>
<P>
<B>High Commissioner in Canberra</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/busuttil.jpg" align=left hspace=10>
Born on 3rd April 1939, George N. Busuttil was educated at the
Lyceum and at the RAF University College Cranwell, where he was
an Officer Cadet in the G.D. (Flying) Branch of the RAF.
<P>
On his return to Malta in 1958, he joined the Civil Service as
a C.O. and was later appointed an Executive Officer after qualifying
in an external examination.      Between 1963-71 he served as
Third Secretary at the Commissioner General's Office in London,
returned to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs as Second Secretary
and was posted back to London until 1971.
<P>
He was promoted to First Secretary in 1971 and transferred to
the Works Department and appointed Assistant Head in 1977 when
he was seconded to the M'Xlokk Project to set-up and run the construction
stage of this Port Project.
<P>
Mr Busuttil returned to the Ministry as Counsellor in 1987 and
was promoted to First Counsellor in 1989.  During this period
he participated in and led various international meetings and
delegations.  He was Acting Secretary (Sept. 1990 to April 1991)
and was appointed High Commissioner for Malta in Canberra in November
1991, High Commissioner for Malta to New Zealand in 1992, and
Ambassador to the Philippines in 1994.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_28"></A>
<B>DR NOEL BUTTIGIEG SCICLUNA</B>
<P>
<B>Permanent Representative to the Council of Europe</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/butigieg.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born in Malta on the
10th January 1951, Noel Buttigieg Scicluna pursued his legal education
at the University of Malta obtaining a doctorate in Law by 1975.
 Within the International sphere, he has fulfilled a number of
posts: Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary, and Permanent
Representative of Malta to the Council of Europe since 1987, Chairman
of Committee of Ministers, Deputies of the Council of Europe 1988;
Dean of the Diplomatic Corp of the Committee of Ministers Deputies
since January 1993; Ambassador of Malta to the Kingdom of the
Netherlands since October 1992; and member of the governing board
of the Social Fund of the Council of Europe since 1990.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_15"></A>
<B>MR VICTOR CAMILLERI</B>
<P>
<B>High Commissioner in London</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/camileri.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Mr Camilleri was born
in 1942. He joined the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, as Second
Secretary, in 1968.  His postings have included Rome, Brussels,
New York, Geneva and London.  He has also served as Permanent
Delegate to UNESCO and to UNIDO, Ambassador to the OSCE, High
Commissioner in London and Permanent Representative to the United
Nations in New York.  Between 1985-87 he served as Acting Secretary
at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and in 1990-91 was Chef de
Cabinet in the Office of the President of the 45th Session of
the General Assembly, Prof. G. de Marco.  He was Permanent
Secretary from 1993 till September 1996.  Mr. Camilleri is married to Elizabeth Bernadette,
and they have two sons.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_30"></A>
<B>DR JOSEPH CASSAR</B>
<P>
<B> Permanent Representative to the U.N. in New York</B>
<P>
Dr Joseph Cassar is Malta's Permanent Representative to the U.N.
in New York since 1993.  He joined the Ministry of Foreign Affairs
in May 1990 when appointed Ambassador to Bulgaria, Czechoslovakia,
Hungary, Poland and Romania.When the Deputy Prime Minister of
Malta was elected President of the 45th Session of the U.N. General
Assembly, he accompanied Prof.  Guido de Marco as Adviser on various
missions, including those to the Occupied Territories and Jordan,
Ethiopia, Kuwait and Albania.  In July 1991, Dr Cassar was appointed
Permanent Representative of Malta to the U.N. in Geneva and Ambassador
to the CSCE.  Ambassador Cassar, who holds a Doctorate in Political
Sciences from the Universita Cattolica del Sacro Cuore (Milan),
was Editorial Director of Independence Press from 1985 to 1991,
and President of the Partit Nazzjonalista's Administrative Council
from 1988 to 1991.  He is married to Tanja nee Ferrante Darbois
and they have two daughters, Mateja and Valentina.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_31"></A>
<B>MR IVES DE BARRO</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador Cairo</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/debarro.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Ives De Barro was born
in Cairo (Egypt) in October 1934 where he received his education
until his departure for Malta in 1950 where he completed his education.
 After a journalistic career which lasted 15 years, he joined
Malta's diplomatic service in July 1967.  He attended a Carnegie
Fellowship in Diplomacy at the Institut des Hautes Etudes Internationales
in Geneva (1967-68).  His first post (as Second Secretary) was
in Tripoli (1969-1974).  Later transferred to Rome (1974-78) as
First Secretary and then a home posting serving in all the Departments
at the Ministry (1978-82).  Boarded out in 1983 he rejoined the
Service in 1987.  Posted to Paris in the same year he was appointed
Counsellor in 1989 and Malta's first resident Ambassador to Egypt
in March 1990.  Ives De Barro, who is married to Anna Maria (nee
Degiorgio) has a daughter and a son.  He speaks Arabic (Egyptian),
French and Italian.<BR><P>

Send an <A HREF="mailto:egidebarro@brainy1.ie-ey.com"><B>e-mail message</B></A>
 to Ambassador De Barro.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_32"></A>
<B>MR GEORGE DOUBLESIN</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador Tripoli</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/dublesin.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born 12th September
1943, assisted in the setting up of the Arabic Language Centre
at the New Lyceum.  Graduated from St. Michael's training college
in 1967, obtaining a B.A. (general) in 1973 and an M.A. from the
University of Malta, with a thesis on linguistics, in 1980.  Between
1978-1980 followed a diploma course in Arabic language and culture
at the University of Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.  In 1988 when seconded
to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, won a scholarship in diplomatic
studies at Oxford University.  On returning to Malta served in
the Arab and African Division of the Ministry.  In March 1991
was posted to Riyadh as Charge' dAffaires.  In April 1994 appointed
Ambassador to Tripoli, also covering relations with Sudan.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_34"></A>
<B> DR JOSEPH LICARI</B>
<P>
<B> Ambassador Paris</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/licari.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Joseph Licari was born
in 1943 and studied at the government primary schools, Vittoriosa
and Cospicua; the Lyceum, Hamrun; and the universities of Malta,
Oxford (Rhodes Scholar) and Paris (Sorbonne).  He holds degrees
in the humanities, economic, political science and law.  Dr Licari
worked as an economist at the Commission of the European Communities
(Brussels), the International Chamber of Commerce (Paris), UNCTAD
(Geneva) and the United Nations (New York). From 1987 to 1991,
Dr Licari was Malta's ambassador to the European Communities in
Brussels and since 1991 he has been Malta's ambassador to France
and Permanent Delegate to UNESCO.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>


<P>
<A NAME="link_37"></A>
<B>MR EVARIST SALIBA</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador Madrid</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/saliba.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born February 1928; underwent
diplomatic training in Oxford (1965-1966).  Set up and ran Malta's
Embassy in Tripoli as <I>Charge d'Affaires</I> (1967-1969 and
1973-1975), Malta's Permanent Mission to the United Nations Office
in Geneva as Permanent Representative and the Embassy in Madrid
as Ambassador since June 1993.  Served as Permanent Secretary
at the Ministry (1987-1989) and later as Adviser (1989-1993) and
non-resident Ambassador to Beijing and PyongYang (1992-1993).
 Participated in many international conferences, notably the CSCE
since 1972, the United Nations General Assembly, UNCTAD, Non-Aligned
and Commonwealth summits.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>

<P>
<A NAME="link_38"></A>
<B>MR GEORGE SALIBA</B>
<P>
<B>Ambassador Moscow</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/saliba-g.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born on the 27th January
1944, George Saliba carried out his educational studies at Plater
College, Oxford (1966-68) and John Hopkins University.  In 1971,
he lectured in Politics and Social Studies at the University and
Polytechnic of Malta respectively. His career with the Foreign
Office commenced as a Public Relations Officer at the Kuwait Embassy
in Malta (1974-76).  Later, in 1981, he became nonresident Ambassador
to the countries of the Arabian Gulf. 1985 saw him as first resident
Ambassador of Malta to Riyadh, on which occasion he was responsible
for the setting up of the Saudi Arabian Embassy.  He served as
Resident Ambassador in Tripoli between 1987 - 1993 and was appointed
Ambassador to Moscow in 1993.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>



<P>
<A NAME="link_40"></A>
<B>DR JOHN VASSALLO</B>
<P>
<B>Permanent Delegate to the European Union</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="amb/vassallo.jpg" align=left hspace=10>Born in Sliema on the
16th July 1948, Dr Vassallo pursued studies at St. Aloysius College,
he attended the University of Malta graduated B.A. in 1968, and
LL.D. in 1973 with a thesis on the &quot;competition law of the
E.E.C. A supranational legislation&quot;.During his postgraduate
studies in Amsterdam, Stockholm and Geneva Dr Vassallo deepened
his knowledge of the E.U. as well as International Management.
 Dr Vassallo spent a number of years in Belgium, Sweden and France
where he was administrative director and later president of a
Swedish Multinational.  After a couple of years working as a lobbyist
for European industries in Brussels Dr Vassallo was nominated
Ambassador of Malta to the E. U. in Brussels in 1993.  His mission
is also accredited to Belgium, Luxembourg, Sweden, Denmark and
Norway.
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR noshade size=5>



