<TITLE>Video On Line - Malta</TITLE>
<!--Author: LJ, VOL - Malta
Date: 14 November 1995
Project: Medgate-->
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<CENTER><H1>Video On Line - Malta</H1></CENTER>

<HR WIDTH=80% ALIGN=center>
<BR>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="volmt256.gif"></IMG></CENTER>
<p>

Video On Line Malta has been formed with the intention of offering the
Internet service to the Maltese islands and eventually spreading the
service to the southern and eastern countries in the Mediterranean. We are
now pleased to be collaborating with the North South Centre in the setting
up of the Internet Cafe for the Med Gate Conference in Barcelona. <p>

We strongly believe that what we are projecting for the Mediterranean is to
have a centrally located Information Technology Hub which can be accessed
by all Government  and Diplomatic Institutions around the Mediterranean.
These may not necessarily be directly in the Mediterranean, however the hub
will give the possibility for countries to centralise Databases and other
data transfer of governmental documents to one another through the
Information Superhighway. We hope to have further collaboration between
Video On Line Malta  and The North South  Centre on other projects in the
future and possibly become one solid information Team. <p>

<HR WIDTH=80% ALIGN=center>
<CENTER>For further information please mail to <a href="mailto:sandrob@vol.vol.it">Video On Line - Malta</a></CENTER>
</DOC>
