<BODY>
<CENTER><H1>MedGate</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><H1>NEWS UPDATE</H1></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=80% ALIGN=center>

<UL>

<!--Copy and paste text from her till next comment marker and repace text as necessary. Please do not delete codes.-->
<DL>
<LI><DT><A HREF="link.htm">ENVIRONMENT (18 August 1995 - 1170 words - IPS Analysis)</A>
<DD><B>Scarcity of water the spark of future conflict</B><BR>
Water is emerging as a potential source of international conflict in the 21st century..."It is not a coincidence that conflict over the control of these resources is, even today, one of the biggest obstacles to peace treaties between Israel and its Arab neighbours," says World Bank Vice President Ismael Serageldin.<P> 
</DL>
<!--Copy and paste till here-->

<DL>
<LI><DT><A HREF="link.htm">EX-YUGOSLAVIA (28 August 1995 - 1180 words - IPS Analysis)</A>
<DD><B>' Caring mummy' has become a wicked stepmother in Serbia</B><BR>
The six coffee cups arranged carefully on the tray are chipped and unmatched, as are the plates laden with sweet pies and fruits, yet the woman and childeren of Kovilovo relish their afternoon ritual as much as they did back home in Benkovac.<P>
</DL>

<DL>
<LI><DT><A HREF="link.htm">PALESTINE (27 August 1995 - 880 words - IPS Report)</A>
<DD><B>Youth get raw deal from new authorities</B><BR>
When a 15 year old Palestine from the West Bank was arrested in Gaza several months ago for theft, Palestine police put him in a rehabilitation centre for days - without telling his parrents.<P>
</DL>

</UL>
<HR WIDTH=80% ALIGN=center>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="medhome.htm">Back to the MedGate home page</A></CENTER>
<P>
