<H3>   INTERNATIONAL SECURITY NETWORK</H3>
<HR>

<P>
Mr.Thomas Koeppel, Coordinator of International Security presented
his paper on International Security Network and highlighted the
following;
<P>
The ISN was established following the International Conference
' Institutes and the Security Dialogue' from 26-28 April 1994.
Among the goals of the ISN;
<P>
 * To exploit international electronic communication it improve
co-operation and interaction among institutions in the fields
of international relations  ,defense ,and security in East and
West.
<P>
 * To link these institutions with governments, military bodies,
and international organizations as well as
<P>
 NGO's and the media.
<P>
 * To provide an infrastructure for information retrieval.
<P>
 * To meet the information needs of East European Institutes.
<P>
 The ISN Offers :
<P>
 * one-stop information network in the fields of defense, peace
aand international security studies as
<P>
 well as international relations.
<P>
 <A HREF="auto5.htm">* Virtual Library</A>.
<P>
 * 24-hour access point to discussion with fellow scientists,
government officials, NGO representatives. 
</BODY>

