<BODY>

<H3>     VIRTUAL LIBRARY</H3>
<HR>

<P>
The ISN offers public access to its virtual library. It is just
what it sounds like; a modern library on the Internet. You can
access over 500 data sources that ISN is referencing. ISN therefore
serves as a supplementary bookshelf, complementing already exicting
libraries as well as providing a basic documentation in places
where specialist liberaries are not available.
<P>
The ISN virtual Library presents informationin two basic modes:
access by subject and access by regions.
