<H1>Titles of contributions :</H1></center>
<HR>

<H2>Themes</H2>

<H3>Development Measures and Drugs Policies:</H3>

<P>
<B>Two Sides of the Same Coin</B>
<UL>
<LI>How can we increase the coherence of drugs policy and development
policy; and what are the consequences for citizens in developing
countries?
<LI>What influence do economic, political, cultural and social
factors have, at both local and international level, in encouraging
drug production, trade and consumption?
<LI>What is the effect of drug production, trade and consumption
on the politics, economies, cultures, societies and the environment
in both North and South?
<LI>How can contradictions between the promotion of democracy/human
rights/environment and international economic policies be reduced?
<LI>What have we achieved in 20 years of repressive anti-drug
measures?
<LI>What contradictions exist between liberal economic measures
and production control?
<LI>How can alternative development strategies be promoted?
<LI>What role can citizens' organisations play? (through empowerment
of people/ participatory democracy).
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="themeb">New Producers, Traders and Consumers</A>
</H3>

<UL>
<LI>The emergence of new producers, new consumers and new criminal
organisations, particularly in Africa and in Central and Eastern
Europe.
<LI>What can be learned from the experiences of Latin America
for future projects in Africa and Central and Eastern Europe?
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="themec">Education, Information and Communication
Strategies</A></H3>

<UL>
<LI>How can a coherent system of information-sharing be set up
in order to avoid duplication of work and increase the complementarity
of different initiatives? (the need for up-to-date information
on the political, economic and ecological aspects of drug production).
<LI>What is the role of the media in the prevention of the consumption
and the supply of drugs?
<LI>How can educational strategies and campaigns to inform the
public on drugs issues be promoted?
<LI>How can the participation of Southern NGOs concerned with
aspects of the drugs trade in public debates in Europe be promoted?
</UL>
<HR>

